This paper is about reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper introduces new operators for Q-functions, which are commonly used in reinforcement learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization and control, which are relevant to categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper introduces new algorithms and provides empirical results, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
